      • close

        public void close()
           throws java.lang.Exception
        Since a connection to the dispatcher is established, this class is defined as AutoCloseable for the sake of convenience. ManagedChannels use resources like threads and TCP connections. To prevent leaking these resources, the channel should be shut down when it will no longer be used. Also, if local garbage collection is enabled, clean local arrow storage
        Specified by:
        close in interface java.lang.AutoCloseable

      • withLocalGC

        public Handler withLocalGC()
        If turned on, the vector will be deleted locally after vectorHandler is shut down. Especially handy, to push data to servers and also save local ram.
        Returns:
        Handler configured to clean up after itself
